But I'm glad to hear someone is interested despite abruptly letting you know.

261
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,760
When the CEO said she was buying this factory,

262
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:31,520
there was actually someone else who wanted to buy it.

263
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:34,140
Oh, that's good.

264
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:39,490
But that person wanted it at a certain price.

265
00:21:39,490 --> 00:21:40,770
It is a bit...

266
00:21:40,770 --> 00:21:42,820
What was the price?

267
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:46,260
It was at half price.

268
00:21:46,260 --> 00:21:47,410
Half price?

269
00:21:47,410 --> 00:21:49,100
Yes.

270
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:53,650
He said he'd buy it if it was half the price that you two bought it for.

271
00:21:53,650 --> 00:21:57,670
As you probably know, a factory like this doesn't have a market value.

272
00:21:57,670 --> 00:22:01,730
At least he said that he can make the payment right away.

273
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:03,760
You should take that into account.

274
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,210
We've got three days left.

275
00:22:14,450 --> 00:22:16,710
Hey! Bong Gyu!

276
00:22:18,660 --> 00:22:20,380
Here, here, here.

277
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:25,810
Hey, why are you suddenly acting like we're buddies?

278
00:22:26,890 --> 00:22:31,180
- Why did you ask to see me?
- Hey, your coffee is so tasty.

279
00:22:32,390 --> 00:22:34,280
What's this?

280
00:22:34,280 --> 00:22:38,940
Wow, I kept thinking about this taste.

281
00:22:38,940 --> 00:22:41,950
Gosh, what did you put in this coffee?

282
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,070
- Hey.
- What?

283
00:22:49,070 --> 00:22:51,330
- Bong Gyu.
- What?

284
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:54,190
Do you have money?

285
00:22:54,190 --> 00:22:55,550
What?

286
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,470
I asked if you have some money?

287
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:05,460
Am I getting mugged? In my own cafe?

288
00:23:05,460 --> 00:23:07,530
I'm not mugging you.

289
00:23:08,340 --> 00:23:10,030
Please help me out.

290
00:23:12,380 --> 00:23:14,940
We're trying to bring Yoo Jin Woo back,

291
00:23:14,940 --> 00:23:16,680
but we're lacking a bit of money.

292
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:18,920
I hear you invest in various places, right?

293
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:21,810
You should invest in us. How about it?

294
00:23:24,410 --> 00:23:27,610
Well, please invest in us.

295
00:23:29,980 --> 00:23:31,620
Why would I?

296
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:36,550
You're right. Why would you invest in me when all I did was housework?

297
00:23:36,550 --> 00:23:38,050
I don't even expect that of you.

298
00:23:38,050 --> 00:23:43,590
But you should consider my wife, CEO Kang Su Hyeon.

299
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:47,790
You've heard from people at Pandora, right?

300
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:51,350
CEO Kang looks at the trainees' eyes to almost an excessive level.

301
00:23:51,350 --> 00:23:53,660
Do you know why she does that?

302
00:23:53,660 --> 00:23:55,610
I heard she's looking to see if they're a sociopath.

303
00:23:55,610 --> 00:23:57,150
That's not it. It's not.

304
00:23:57,150 --> 00:23:59,620
She did that even when I was at the company.

305
00:23:59,620 --> 00:24:02,890
CEO Kang wants to see into the future of the trainees.

306
00:24:02,890 --> 00:24:04,730
Rather than someone who can be profitable right away,

307
00:24:04,730 --> 00:24:07,930
she chooses trainees who can sustain themselves after becoming adults.

308
00:24:07,930 --> 00:24:11,360
She knows how to look that far ahead.

309
00:24:13,630 --> 00:24:16,980
Even if we can't earn you a lot of money right away,

310
00:24:16,980 --> 00:24:19,110
you won't regret it.

311
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:30,970
I'm telling you, you won't regret it.

312
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,700
Hey,

313
00:24:35,610 --> 00:24:38,770
you know that Jang Hyeon Cheol is trying to take Yoo Jin Woo, too, right?

314
00:24:38,770 --> 00:24:40,550
Do you know why?

315
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:45,440
He's determined that Yoo Jin Woo is profitable even though he's down and out.

316
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:47,750
He's an expert in that field.

317
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:50,180
He knows what happens at the bottom of the

318
00:24:50,180 --> 00:24:54,330
entertainment world and where the money flows.

319
00:24:54,330 --> 00:24:57,120
Though your offer seems interesting,

320
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,220
it doesn't seem like it'll be profitable right away.

321
00:24:59,220 --> 00:25:01,550
Jang Hyeon Cheol's offer

322
00:25:02,580 --> 00:25:06,380
